WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.000
Cambridge English readers start a level.

00:04.000 --> 00:06.000
Why?

00:06.000 --> 00:08.000
Bifillip Mouse

00:08.000 --> 00:12.000
Published by Cambridge University Press.

00:24.000 --> 00:26.000
Why?

00:26.000 --> 00:28.000
Bifillip Mouse

00:30.000 --> 00:32.000
Bifillip Mouse

00:39.000 --> 00:41.000
Chapter 1

00:41.000 --> 00:43.000
Goodbye.

00:44.000 --> 00:47.000
Please don't go to Glossia.

00:47.000 --> 00:49.000
Says Sara.

00:49.000 --> 00:52.000
You're only 19.

00:52.000 --> 00:58.000
Alex is saying goodbye to Sara, his girlfriend.

00:58.000 --> 01:00.000
I must.

01:00.000 --> 01:02.000
Answer Alex.

01:02.000 --> 01:04.000
I'm a soldier.

01:04.000 --> 01:06.000
It's my job.

01:06.000 --> 01:09.000
I must go where the army says.

01:09.000 --> 01:13.000
But why are you going there?

01:13.000 --> 01:15.000
Ask Sara.

01:15.000 --> 01:18.000
We're going to stop the fighting.

01:18.000 --> 01:20.000
Says Alex.

01:20.000 --> 01:23.000
Lots of people are dying.

01:23.000 --> 01:27.000
But why are they fighting?

01:27.000 --> 01:29.000
Ask Sara.

01:29.000 --> 01:31.000
I don't know.

01:31.000 --> 01:33.000
Answer Alex.

01:33.000 --> 01:35.000
Why don't you ask?

01:35.000 --> 01:37.000
Says Sara.

01:37.000 --> 01:40.000
You never ask questions.

01:40.000 --> 01:42.000
I know.

01:42.000 --> 01:44.000
Answer Alex.

01:44.000 --> 01:46.000
I'm sorry.

01:46.000 --> 01:48.000
I hate asking questions.

01:48.000 --> 01:51.000
Please change Alex.

01:51.000 --> 01:53.000
Says Sara.

01:53.000 --> 01:55.000
For me.

01:56.000 --> 01:59.000
I'm going to think about you every day.

01:59.000 --> 02:01.000
Says Sara.

02:01.000 --> 02:03.000
Me too.

02:03.000 --> 02:05.000
Alex answers.

02:05.000 --> 02:08.000
I can send you a text from my phone tomorrow.

02:08.000 --> 02:11.000
And I think there's email.

02:11.000 --> 02:13.000
That's good.

02:13.000 --> 02:16.000
Sara says with a little smile.

02:16.000 --> 02:19.000
I love you, Alex.

02:19.000 --> 02:21.000
And I love you too.

02:21.000 --> 02:23.000
Answer Alex.

02:23.000 --> 02:31.000
Now, don't be sad.

02:31.000 --> 02:33.000
Chapter 2.

02:33.000 --> 02:36.000
We're in glossia now.

02:36.000 --> 02:40.000
Alex is on the plane to glossia.

02:40.000 --> 02:43.000
He's sitting next to Sergeant Ken.

02:43.000 --> 02:48.000
It's Ken's second time in glossia.

02:49.000 --> 02:51.000
Excuse me, Sergeant.

02:51.000 --> 02:53.000
Alex starts.

02:53.000 --> 02:56.000
You can call me Ken.

02:56.000 --> 02:58.000
The Sergeant says.

02:58.000 --> 03:02.000
Why are they fighting in glossia?

03:02.000 --> 03:04.000
Alex asks.

03:04.000 --> 03:08.000
That's not an easy question.

03:08.000 --> 03:10.000
Ken answers.

03:10.000 --> 03:13.000
I think it's like this.

03:13.000 --> 03:16.000
Some people have guns.

03:16.000 --> 03:20.000
They use the guns because they want something.

03:20.000 --> 03:25.000
Then other people get guns to fight back with.

03:25.000 --> 03:28.000
Now everyone has guns.

03:28.000 --> 03:33.000
And everyone forgets what they are fighting about.

03:33.000 --> 03:36.000
But where do the guns come from?

03:36.000 --> 03:39.000
Is Alex's next question?

03:39.000 --> 03:45.000
People from other countries sell them to the glossions.

03:45.000 --> 03:47.000
Ken answers.

03:47.000 --> 03:48.000
Why?

03:48.000 --> 03:50.000
asks Alex.

03:50.000 --> 03:53.000
Ken smiles.

03:53.000 --> 03:54.000
Money.

03:54.000 --> 03:56.000
That's why.

03:56.000 --> 04:01.000
Ken, can we stop people buying and selling guns?

04:01.000 --> 04:03.000
Alex asks.

04:03.000 --> 04:05.000
No, we can't.

04:05.000 --> 04:11.000
The people who sell the guns, they're thousands of kilometers away.

04:11.000 --> 04:16.000
All we can do is help the people here in this country.

04:16.000 --> 04:19.000
Answers, Ken.

04:19.000 --> 04:24.000
We're going to a famous old town called Tonic.

04:24.000 --> 04:29.000
In Tonic, lots of people are fighting each other.

04:29.000 --> 04:34.000
And some of them are also fighting us.

04:34.000 --> 04:40.000
There's a very loud noise, and the plane goes over to the right.

04:40.000 --> 04:42.000
What's that?

04:42.000 --> 04:44.000
Shouts Alex.

04:44.000 --> 04:46.000
What do you think?

04:46.000 --> 04:48.000
Answers, Ken.

04:48.000 --> 04:52.000
We're in glossier now.

04:52.000 --> 04:54.000
Is it always like this?

04:54.000 --> 04:56.000
Alex asks.

04:56.000 --> 04:57.000
Yes?

04:57.000 --> 04:59.000
Ken answers.

04:59.000 --> 05:04.000
But the papers say the glossion people want us here.

05:04.000 --> 05:06.000
Alex says.

05:06.000 --> 05:09.000
The sergeant smiles.

05:09.000 --> 05:13.000
Some glossions do, and some don't.

05:13.000 --> 05:15.000
Answers, Ken.

05:15.000 --> 05:19.000
But we're here to help all the people.

05:19.000 --> 05:22.000
And is it always hot?

05:22.000 --> 05:24.000
asks Alex.

05:24.000 --> 05:26.000
Yes.

05:26.000 --> 05:28.000
Laughs, Ken.

05:32.000 --> 05:34.000
Chapter 3.

05:34.000 --> 05:38.000
Soldiers get out.

05:38.000 --> 05:42.000
Sergeant Ken and Alex drive into Tonic.

05:42.000 --> 05:45.000
People watch them.

05:45.000 --> 05:53.000
Alex, this is where you're living for the next six months, says Ken.

05:53.000 --> 05:59.000
Your bed's over there, and this is Hawk.

05:59.000 --> 06:06.000
A tall man with very short hair stands up and puts out his hand.

06:06.000 --> 06:07.000
Hi.

06:07.000 --> 06:09.000
He says.

06:09.000 --> 06:12.000
Ah, that's Stefan on the bed.

06:12.000 --> 06:14.000
Ken says.

06:14.000 --> 06:18.000
Stefan smiles at Alex.

06:18.000 --> 06:19.000
Hello?

06:19.000 --> 06:21.000
Put your things down.

06:21.000 --> 06:23.000
He says.

06:23.000 --> 06:26.000
Do you want something to eat or drink?

06:26.000 --> 06:28.000
Yes, please.

06:28.000 --> 06:30.000
Answers, Alex.

06:30.000 --> 06:32.000
I'm going now.

06:32.000 --> 06:34.000
Ken says.

06:34.000 --> 06:36.000
You must be tired, Alex.

06:36.000 --> 06:39.000
Try and get some sleep tonight.

06:39.000 --> 06:43.000
We start work in the morning.

06:43.000 --> 06:45.000
Hi, Sarah.

06:45.000 --> 06:48.000
It's very hot in glossia.

06:48.000 --> 06:52.000
Sergeant Ken says we're here to help.

06:52.000 --> 06:54.000
But can we?

06:54.000 --> 06:57.000
I don't know.

06:57.000 --> 07:00.000
All my love, Alex.

07:05.000 --> 07:07.000
Chapter 4.

07:07.000 --> 07:10.000
First Patrol.

07:10.000 --> 07:15.000
The next day, it's time for Alex's first patrol.

07:15.000 --> 07:18.000
Just do what I do.

07:18.000 --> 07:20.000
Ken tells Alex.

07:20.000 --> 07:25.000
Stefan and Hawk are going to walk behind us.

07:25.000 --> 07:30.000
Use your eyes and ears and look everywhere.

07:30.000 --> 07:37.000
And don't forget, we never know who is a friend and who isn't.

07:37.000 --> 07:40.000
What are we looking for?

07:40.000 --> 07:43.000
Ask Alex.

07:43.000 --> 07:45.000
Gums.

07:45.000 --> 07:48.000
Answers, Ken, with a quick laugh.

07:48.000 --> 07:50.000
And gunman.

07:50.000 --> 07:52.000
Hawk says.

07:52.000 --> 07:55.000
He isn't laughing.

07:55.000 --> 07:59.000
But what about the people who sell the guns?

07:59.000 --> 08:01.000
Alex asks.

08:01.000 --> 08:03.000
They're not here.

08:03.000 --> 08:05.000
Hawk answers.

08:05.000 --> 08:10.000
They're far away with their money.

08:10.000 --> 08:14.000
Some people are happy to see the soldiers.

08:14.000 --> 08:17.000
They stop and say hello.

08:17.000 --> 08:22.000
But some boys aren't happy that the soldiers are there.

08:22.000 --> 08:26.000
They're throwing things at the patrol and shouting.

08:26.000 --> 08:32.000
The soldiers don't understand what the boys are shouting.

08:32.000 --> 08:35.000
Something hits Alex in the mouth.

08:35.000 --> 08:38.000
He turns with his gun.

08:38.000 --> 08:43.000
Alex isn't slow, but the boys are very fast.

08:43.000 --> 08:45.000
They run away.

08:45.000 --> 08:48.000
Alex feels his mouth.

08:48.000 --> 08:50.000
Are you okay?

08:50.000 --> 08:52.000
Stefan shouts.

08:52.000 --> 08:54.000
Yes!

08:54.000 --> 08:56.000
Answers, Alex.

08:56.000 --> 08:59.000
Then they hear a gun.

08:59.000 --> 09:03.000
Someone's shooting at them.

09:03.000 --> 09:08.000
Alex looks across the dirty street at a house.

09:08.000 --> 09:13.000
He sees someone at a bedroom window.

09:13.000 --> 09:14.000
Look!

09:14.000 --> 09:15.000
Up there!

09:15.000 --> 09:17.000
Alex shouts.

09:17.000 --> 09:22.000
Hawk turns, looks up, and shoots at the window.

09:22.000 --> 09:27.000
Ken and Alex run across the street to the house.

09:27.000 --> 09:32.000
They open the front door and run up to the bedroom.

09:32.000 --> 09:37.000
Hawk and Stefan wait in the street.

09:37.000 --> 09:39.000
Hi, Sarah.

09:39.000 --> 09:41.000
What a bad day.

09:41.000 --> 09:44.000
My first patrol.

09:44.000 --> 09:49.000
There's shooting, and I see someone at a bedroom window.

09:49.000 --> 09:52.000
Hawk shoots at the window.

09:52.000 --> 09:57.000
Then Ken and I run into the house and up to the bedroom.

09:57.000 --> 10:00.000
But there isn't a gunman there.

10:00.000 --> 10:03.000
It's a little boy.

10:03.000 --> 10:07.000
The boy's mother comes and shouts at us.

10:07.000 --> 10:13.000
I don't understand what she's saying, but I can see she's very angry.

10:14.000 --> 10:19.000
I want to say sorry, but I don't speak glossion.

10:19.000 --> 10:25.000
When we leave, the woman is shouting and the small boy is crying.

10:25.000 --> 10:27.000
I don't feel well.

10:27.000 --> 10:29.000
It's all wrong.

10:29.000 --> 10:32.000
What am I doing here?

10:32.000 --> 10:40.000
All my love, Alex.

10:40.000 --> 10:45.000
Chapter 5. We have no names.

10:45.000 --> 10:53.000
The next day, Sergeant Ken, Alex, Hawk, and Stefan are on patrol again.

10:53.000 --> 10:56.000
It's 12 o'clock.

10:56.000 --> 11:01.000
A kilometer away, a family is finishing lunch.

11:01.000 --> 11:09.000
There's a 12-year-old boy called Happy and an 8-year-old girl called Marina.

11:09.000 --> 11:14.000
Their mother's name is Ada, and she's very beautiful.

11:14.000 --> 11:17.000
There's no father.

11:17.000 --> 11:20.000
He's dead.

11:20.000 --> 11:26.000
In the afternoon, Ada puts away the lunch things and makes coffee.

11:26.000 --> 11:32.000
Happy is sitting on the floor in the living room with Marina.

11:32.000 --> 11:37.000
The brother and sister are laughing and playing with a doll.

11:37.000 --> 11:41.000
Ada doesn't hear the back door.

11:41.000 --> 11:43.000
Two men come in.

11:43.000 --> 11:47.000
One is tall and one is short.

11:47.000 --> 11:50.000
The short man has a bag.

11:50.000 --> 11:58.000
They're wearing white t-shirts and black trousers, and they have black masks.

11:58.000 --> 12:01.000
Ada looks at the two men.

12:01.000 --> 12:07.000
Then she shouts to her children, come here now!

12:07.000 --> 12:12.000
Happy and Marina run to their mother and stand by her.

12:12.000 --> 12:16.000
They're afraid of the two men in masks.

12:16.000 --> 12:19.000
Who are you?

12:19.000 --> 12:22.000
Ada asks the men.

12:22.000 --> 12:24.000
They don't answer.

12:24.000 --> 12:31.000
The short man puts the bag down, and the tall man looks at Ada.

12:31.000 --> 12:34.000
What are your names?

12:34.000 --> 12:36.000
asks Ada.

12:36.000 --> 12:42.000
We have no names, and we have no faces.

12:42.000 --> 12:45.000
Answers the tall man.

12:45.000 --> 12:48.000
We are not rich.

12:48.000 --> 12:50.000
What do you want?

12:50.000 --> 12:53.000
asks Ada.

12:53.000 --> 12:58.000
Nothing answers the short man.

12:58.000 --> 13:08.000
All we want is your house for ten minutes.

13:08.000 --> 13:10.000
Chapter 6

13:10.000 --> 13:14.000
Don't ask stupid questions.

13:15.000 --> 13:20.000
A young woman with a baby comes in the front door.

13:20.000 --> 13:22.000
Who's she?

13:22.000 --> 13:24.000
asks Ada.

13:24.000 --> 13:28.000
Shh, says the tall man.

13:28.000 --> 13:31.000
The baby.

13:31.000 --> 13:34.000
The young woman takes up the baby.

13:34.000 --> 13:36.000
It's sleeping.

13:36.000 --> 13:41.000
Under the baby is a long gun.

13:41.000 --> 13:47.000
The tall man takes the gun, and the woman puts the baby down again.

13:47.000 --> 13:51.000
What are you going to do?

13:51.000 --> 13:53.000
asks Happy.

13:53.000 --> 13:56.000
A soldier's going to die.

13:56.000 --> 13:59.000
Answers the short man.

13:59.000 --> 14:01.000
Why?

14:01.000 --> 14:03.000
asks Happy.

14:03.000 --> 14:09.000
Don't ask stupid questions, says the tall man.

14:09.000 --> 14:12.000
This is our country.

14:12.000 --> 14:18.000
We don't want soldiers from other countries here.

14:18.000 --> 14:22.000
You, the short man shouts to Marina.

14:22.000 --> 14:26.000
Give me your doll.

14:26.000 --> 14:28.000
Do it!

14:28.000 --> 14:31.000
Ada tells her daughter.

14:31.000 --> 14:34.000
Marina gives the man her doll.

14:34.000 --> 14:40.000
He takes something out of his bag and puts it in the doll.

14:40.000 --> 14:46.000
Then he takes a phone and puts it in the doll too.

14:46.000 --> 14:49.000
Listen, you too.

14:49.000 --> 14:52.000
The short man tells the children.

14:52.000 --> 14:55.000
You mustn't play with the doll now.

14:55.000 --> 14:58.000
Do you understand?

14:58.000 --> 15:00.000
Yes!

15:00.000 --> 15:02.000
Happy answers.

15:02.000 --> 15:08.000
Here, the short man says to the young woman with the baby.

15:08.000 --> 15:14.000
Take the doll and leave it in the street in front of the house.

15:14.000 --> 15:19.000
The short man speaks to the children.

15:19.000 --> 15:23.000
Go and play in front of the house now.

15:23.000 --> 15:29.000
But when you see the soldiers, you must run in again.

15:29.000 --> 15:31.000
He looks at Ada.

15:31.000 --> 15:38.000
Then you take your children out of the house by the back door.

15:38.000 --> 15:40.000
Do you understand?

15:40.000 --> 15:42.000
Yes!

15:42.000 --> 15:44.000
Says Ada.

15:44.000 --> 15:47.000
Happy and Marina.

15:47.000 --> 15:51.000
Go out and play in the street now.

15:51.000 --> 15:55.000
But don't go near the doll.

15:56.000 --> 16:00.000
The short man gives a phone to the tall man.

16:00.000 --> 16:05.000
This phone's for you, and there's a phone in the doll.

16:05.000 --> 16:07.000
He says.

16:07.000 --> 16:13.000
The tall man takes the gun and the phone up to the bedroom.

16:13.000 --> 16:17.000
The young woman goes with him.

16:17.000 --> 16:22.000
Out of the window, they can see the children in the street.

16:22.000 --> 16:25.000
And the doll.

16:25.000 --> 16:30.000
The tall man has the phone in his hand.

16:30.000 --> 16:36.000
All we can do now is await, he tells the woman.

16:36.000 --> 16:38.000
Listen!

16:38.000 --> 16:40.000
What's that?

16:40.000 --> 16:42.000
asks the woman.

16:42.000 --> 16:44.000
Can you hear something?

16:44.000 --> 16:48.000
Yes, the tall man answers.

16:48.000 --> 16:50.000
It's the soldiers.

16:50.000 --> 16:57.000
They're coming.

16:57.000 --> 16:59.000
Chapter 7.

16:59.000 --> 17:02.000
They're afraid of us.

17:02.000 --> 17:05.000
Why are the children running away?

17:05.000 --> 17:08.000
Alex asks Hawk.

17:08.000 --> 17:11.000
Because they're afraid of us!

17:11.000 --> 17:13.000
Hawk answers.

17:13.000 --> 17:15.000
But why?

17:15.000 --> 17:18.000
Alex, we're here to help.

17:18.000 --> 17:22.000
Don't they know that we're their friends?

17:22.000 --> 17:26.000
The patrol gets near to Ada's house.

17:26.000 --> 17:28.000
Yes!

17:28.000 --> 17:31.000
The children must be afraid of us.

17:31.000 --> 17:34.000
Alex says to Hawk.

17:34.000 --> 17:35.000
Look!

17:35.000 --> 17:38.000
That's their doll in the street.

17:38.000 --> 17:40.000
I'm going to give it to them.

17:40.000 --> 17:44.000
Then they can see we're their friends.

17:45.000 --> 17:48.000
Alex runs over to the doll.

17:49.000 --> 17:51.000
Stop!

17:51.000 --> 17:53.000
Shouts Ken.

17:53.000 --> 17:55.000
Alex looks up.

17:55.000 --> 17:56.000
Why?

17:56.000 --> 17:58.000
He asks.

17:58.000 --> 18:01.000
I'm just trying to help.

18:01.000 --> 18:03.000
Do what I say!

18:03.000 --> 18:05.000
Shouts Ken.

18:05.000 --> 18:08.000
Come here now!

18:08.000 --> 18:13.000
Up in the bedroom, the tall man speaks to the young woman.

18:14.000 --> 18:18.000
The phone isn't working!

18:18.000 --> 18:21.000
He's very angry.

18:21.000 --> 18:24.000
What about the gun?

18:24.000 --> 18:27.000
The young woman asks.

18:27.000 --> 18:30.000
The tall man looks at Hawk.

18:30.000 --> 18:32.000
Then it's Stefan.

18:32.000 --> 18:35.000
Then Sergeant Ken.

18:35.000 --> 18:40.000
Then he looks at Alex and chooses.

18:40.000 --> 18:46.000
You're going to die, he says.

18:46.000 --> 18:49.000
The tall man shoots.

18:49.000 --> 18:54.000
Alex's mouth opens and he tries to say something.

18:54.000 --> 18:58.000
Then his eyes close.

18:58.000 --> 19:01.000
He doesn't say anything.

19:01.000 --> 19:04.000
He doesn't see anything.

19:04.000 --> 19:07.000
He doesn't feel anything.

19:07.000 --> 19:10.000
He's dead.

19:10.000 --> 19:13.000
Hawk turns and looks up.

19:13.000 --> 19:18.000
He sees someone at the bedroom window.

19:18.000 --> 19:20.000
Up there!

19:20.000 --> 19:24.000
Hawk shouts and shoots.

19:24.000 --> 19:30.000
Then Ken and Stefan shoot at the window.

19:30.000 --> 19:36.000
The young woman helps the tall man down to the living room.

19:37.000 --> 19:39.000
Here!

19:39.000 --> 19:41.000
Quick!

19:41.000 --> 19:43.000
Take the gun!

19:43.000 --> 19:46.000
He says to the young woman.

19:46.000 --> 19:51.000
She takes the gun and puts it under the baby.

19:51.000 --> 19:53.000
Come on!

19:53.000 --> 19:55.000
The soldiers are coming!

19:55.000 --> 19:57.000
Shouts the short man.

19:57.000 --> 20:01.000
You must see a doctor!

20:01.000 --> 20:05.000
I can't go anywhere!

20:05.000 --> 20:07.000
The tall man says.

20:07.000 --> 20:09.000
You two go!

20:09.000 --> 20:12.000
Now!

20:12.000 --> 20:20.000
He closes his eyes.

20:20.000 --> 20:22.000
Chapter 8.

20:22.000 --> 20:26.000
Don't say anything.

20:26.000 --> 20:32.000
The young woman and the short man run out of the back of the house.

20:32.000 --> 20:37.000
Ada and the children are waiting there.

20:37.000 --> 20:39.000
Where's your friend?

20:39.000 --> 20:42.000
Ada asks.

20:42.000 --> 20:43.000
Dead.

20:43.000 --> 20:46.000
The young woman answers.

20:46.000 --> 20:48.000
Why?

20:48.000 --> 20:50.000
Asks happy.

20:50.000 --> 20:53.000
Because of the soldiers.

20:53.000 --> 20:56.000
The young woman says.

20:56.000 --> 21:01.000
She turns and walks away fast with the baby.

21:01.000 --> 21:04.000
I hate soldiers.

21:04.000 --> 21:06.000
Happy says.

21:06.000 --> 21:10.000
Don't tell the soldiers about us.

21:10.000 --> 21:13.000
The short man tells Ada.

21:13.000 --> 21:19.000
He takes off his mask and she can see his face now.

21:19.000 --> 21:22.000
And your boy's coming with me.

21:22.000 --> 21:28.000
Don't say anything to the soldiers or he dies.

21:28.000 --> 21:32.000
He takes happy's hand and starts to run off.

21:32.000 --> 21:34.000
No!

21:34.000 --> 21:36.000
Shouts Ada.

21:36.000 --> 21:38.000
Don't take him!

21:38.000 --> 21:40.000
Happy!

21:40.000 --> 21:46.000
Ken, Hawk and Stefan run in the front door of the house.

21:46.000 --> 21:49.000
They see the dead man in the living room.

21:49.000 --> 21:52.000
Stefan runs up to the bedroom.

21:52.000 --> 21:57.000
Hawk and Ken go out to the back of the house.

21:57.000 --> 22:01.000
They find Ada and Marina there.

22:01.000 --> 22:05.000
Hawk speaks a little glossion.

22:05.000 --> 22:07.000
Where are they?

22:07.000 --> 22:09.000
He shouts.

22:09.000 --> 22:12.000
Ada says nothing.

22:12.000 --> 22:16.000
Then Hawk sees two people running away.

22:16.000 --> 22:19.000
A man and a boy.

22:19.000 --> 22:22.000
Hawk doesn't wait.

22:22.000 --> 22:24.000
He shoots.

22:24.000 --> 22:26.000
No!

22:26.000 --> 22:29.000
Ada shouts.

22:29.000 --> 22:35.000
Ken takes Ada and Marina into the house.

22:35.000 --> 22:39.000
Half an hour later, two kilometers away,

22:39.000 --> 22:43.000
the young woman is walking with the baby.

22:43.000 --> 22:48.000
Two soldiers see her and ask her to stop.

22:48.000 --> 22:50.000
Where are you going?

22:50.000 --> 22:53.000
asks one of the soldiers.

22:53.000 --> 22:55.000
To the shops.

22:55.000 --> 22:57.000
Answers the woman.

22:57.000 --> 23:01.000
I'm going to buy some food.

23:01.000 --> 23:04.000
She smiles at the soldiers.

23:04.000 --> 23:06.000
What's in there?

23:06.000 --> 23:08.000
The soldier shouts.

23:08.000 --> 23:10.000
My baby.

23:10.000 --> 23:12.000
The woman says.

23:12.000 --> 23:14.000
Please don't shout.

23:14.000 --> 23:17.000
He's sleeping.

23:17.000 --> 23:20.000
She smiles again.

23:20.000 --> 23:23.000
Okay. You can go.

23:23.000 --> 23:33.000
Says one of the soldiers and smiles at her.

23:33.000 --> 23:35.000
Chapter 9.

23:35.000 --> 23:37.000
Why?

23:37.000 --> 23:42.000
There are lots of soldiers at Ada's house now.

23:42.000 --> 23:47.000
They take Alex and the tall man away in a car.

23:47.000 --> 23:51.000
A glossy man is helping Sergeant Ken.

23:51.000 --> 23:55.000
He's asking Ada lots of questions.

23:55.000 --> 23:59.000
But Ada doesn't answer.

23:59.000 --> 24:03.000
All she can think of is happy.

24:03.000 --> 24:05.000
Where is he?

24:05.000 --> 24:07.000
Is he dead?

24:07.000 --> 24:12.000
She takes Marina's hand and listens to the questions.

24:12.000 --> 24:15.000
But she doesn't answer.

24:15.000 --> 24:20.000
The soldiers leave Ada and Marina in the house.

24:20.000 --> 24:25.000
That evening Ada hears a noise at the back door.

24:25.000 --> 24:27.000
It's dark.

24:27.000 --> 24:32.000
She opens the door and sees happy there.

24:32.000 --> 24:35.000
Are the soldiers here?

24:35.000 --> 24:37.000
asks happy.

24:37.000 --> 24:39.000
No.

24:39.000 --> 24:44.000
Ada says with a big smile and takes happy in her arms.

24:44.000 --> 24:54.000
Alex, why don't you answer my emails?

24:54.000 --> 24:56.000
Are you okay?

24:56.000 --> 24:59.000
Why don't you write?

24:59.000 --> 25:01.000
Why?

25:01.000 --> 25:03.000
Why?

25:03.000 --> 25:05.000
All my love.

25:05.000 --> 25:08.000
Sara.

